The paper deals with the design of data center network topologies to achieve high throughput, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and data centers (cs.DC). The paper also involves the analysis of network performance, which could fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper explores the use of random graphs as building blocks for network design, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
